{"source_key":"sha256-f88bd5c54ac5fbbfc982c6d403b2565f","record_index":653,"record_hash":"sha256:d3cba9bc9e1fc03ca8023292787dcabd4f6f3e6396ef3ebc807ccff5a45d7e33","timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:06:27.434Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"{\"status\":{\"[REDACTED:entropy]\":{\"completed\":\"I did the adversarial pass directly. No edits made.\\n\\nVerdict: **buildable, but the acceptance criteria are still too soft for an agentic implementation.** The doc tells the right story; it needs sharper test hooks.\\n\\n**Biggest Gaps**\\n\\n1. **Route parsing is under-tested.**  \\n   [Acceptance Criteria](</Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 Active/agent-session-capture/agent-trail.md:678>) says parse `/<owner>/<repo>/pull/<number>`, but not the rejection matrix.\\n\\n   Add criteria: accepts trailing slash/query/hash normalization; rejects non-numeric PRs, extra path segments, encoded slashes, path traversal, arbitrary git URLs, and non-GitHub-shaped routes.\\n\\n2. **GitHub lookup failure states need status semantics.**  \\n   [Failure States](</Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 Active/agent-session-capture/agent-trail.md:617>) combines “not found” and “lookup failed.” Tests need separate behavior.\\n\\n   Add criteria: `404` from GitHub returns “not public or not found”; `403/429/5xx` returns retryable lookup failure; private repos are not claimed unless GitHub explicitly says private.\\n\\n3. **Fork rejection needs a hard test.**  \\n   The doc says no forks, but branch fallback could accidentally use `head.ref`.\\n\\n   Add criteria: if `head.repo.full_name != base.repo.full_name`, return unsupported before branch lookup; do not query `ref:refs/heads/<fork-branch>` against base metadata.\\n\\n4. **Metadata fetch behavior is still too implementation-loose.**  \\n   [Server-Side Metadata Fetch](</Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 Active/agent-session-capture/agent-trail.md:276>) says fetch `refs/meta/main`, but tests should prove the server does not do a sloppy clone.\\n\\n   Add criteria: initialize bare/cache repo; fetch only `refs/meta/main`; no checkout, hooks, submodules, LFS, or arbitrary remotes; remote URL is constructed from GitHub’s canonical `full_name`.\\n\\n5. **Snapshot refresh semantics are half-deferred.**  \\n   The doc says lat\n[TRUNCATED]\n drill-down” and “too much data” appear, but there are no limits to test.\\n\\n   Add criteria: implementation defines constants for max sessions, turns per session, records per turn, and bytes per record/tool output; truncated responses expose `truncated: true` or equivalent UI state.\\n\\n8. **`but-agentlog` projection contract needs a minimum test shape.**  \\n   The doc defers exact payload, but Forge cannot be tested without minimum fields.\\n\\n   Add criteria: projection includes stable session id, stable turn id, timestamps, match reasons, strength, compact display records, expandable record handles, and redaction-safe text only.\\n\\n9. **Redaction guarantees need fixture tests.**  \\n   [Privacy And Publication](</Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 Active/agent-session-capture/agent-trail.md:552>) makes `but-agentlog` load-bearing. Good, but dangerous without tests.\\n\\n   Add criteria: fixtures containing local paths, provider session ids, hidden/system/developer prompts, and oversized tool output must not render through the public projection.\\n\\n10. **Noindex is missing from acceptance.**  \\n   [line 579](</Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 Active/agent-session-capture/agent-trail.md:579>) says public but not promoted.\\n\\n   Add criteria: rendered pages include `noindex`, via header or meta tag, with a test.\\n\\n**Test Plan I’d Want**\\n\\n- Unit tests: route parsing, canonicalization, target construction, ranking/dedupe.\\n- GitHub API mock tests: public PR, private/not found, fork PR, rate limit, outage.\\n- Git fetch tests: exact `refs/meta/main` fetch, missing ref, fetch failure, OID pinning.\\n- Projection tests: public/read output shape, redaction fixtures, truncation flags.\\n- Page tests: PR identity, snapshot OID, status state, match badges, weak branch separation, bounded evidence drawer.\\n- Concurrency test: two first requests for the same repo share/lock initialization.\\n\\nNo must-ask questions from me before building. These are doc hardening items, not product blockers.\"}},\"timed_out\":false}","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:06:27.434Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}